cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.LG

This paper proposes a method for creating interpretable control agents using a novel recurrent neural network instance. The paper focuses on using this method for governing reinforcement learning tasks, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of search-based RL algorithms, which could also place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The application of the method to autonomous parking of a real rover robot suggests that it could belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. The paper also discusses the theoretical properties of the neuronal circuit policies, which could place it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper compares the performance of the proposed method to deep neural network policies, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
